Class InverseComparator

java.lang.Object

public class InverseComparator
extends Object

The InverseComparator inverts the ordering of a given Comparator.

Field Detail

DEFAULT_INSTANCE

public static final InverseComparator DEFAULT_INSTANCE
This instance can be used for getting a default instance of InverseComparator. It is similar to the Singleton Design Pattern (for further details see Creational Patterns, Prototype in Design Patterns: Elements of Reusable Object-Oriented Software by Erich Gamma, Richard Helm, Ralph Johnson, and John Vlissides) except that there are no mechanisms to avoid the creation of other instances of InverseComparator.
